        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 23 at 8:28PM CST by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 828 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Dawn, or 12 miles northeast of Hereford, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Canyon, Umbarger, Buffalo Lake, Dawn, and Mescalero Park.

This includes Interstate 27 between mile markers 101 and 102, and
between mile markers 106 and 112.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
